---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const title = 'About The Best Mowers - Independent UK Mower Buying Guides';
const description = 'About The Best Mowers: research-led, independent UK lawn mower buying guides built from manufacturer specs, verified owner reviews and retail data. No sponsored placements.';
const path = '/about/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'About', url: path },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished }),
].filter(Boolean);
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} schema={schema}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">About The Best Mowers</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Independent, research-led lawn mower buying guides for UK gardens. No sponsored placements, no manufacturer influence, no copy-pasted retailer feeds. We specialise in cordless and battery mowers, the default choice for most British lawns.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>
        The Best Mowers is a UK lawn mower resource focused on cutting through the noise. There are hundreds of mowers on sale and most "best of" lists are thin and interchangeable. Our job is to do the legwork: read the spec sheets, dig through verified owner reviews, track UK pricing, and turn it into clear, honest advice on the mower that actually suits your garden and budget.
      </p>

      <h2>How we research and choose</h2>
      <p>
        We are a research-led publication, not a test lab, and we are straight about that. Our recommendations are built from three sources, cross-checked against each other:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturer specifications</strong> for the hard numbers: voltage, cutting width, battery capacity, claimed runtime, weight and deck material.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified owner reviews</strong> on Amazon UK and retailer sites, where the real-world picture shows up: battery fade, build niggles, how a mower copes with damp British grass.</li>
        <li><strong>UK retail and pricing data</strong>, so the price bands and value calls reflect what you will actually pay, not an RRP nobody charges.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Where a figure is a manufacturer claim rather than an independent measurement, we say so. Runtime in particular depends on grass length, dampness and cut height, so we describe it as a coverage estimate, not a guarantee. We update picks when models are discontinued or superseded.
      </p>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>
      <p>
        We earn an affiliate commission when you buy a mower through some of our links, at no extra cost to you. It keeps the site running. It never decides the order of a list or which mower we recommend. No manufacturer pays for placement, and no brand has editorial approval over what we publish. See our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">full affiliate disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Our editorial standards</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Every spec is sourced from the manufacturer or a verified retailer listing; claims are labelled as claims.</li>
        <li>We do not fabricate hands-on testing we have not done.</li>
        <li>We update guides as models are superseded and remove discontinued mowers.</li>
        <li>Prices are shown as bands, not live figures; always check the retailer for the current price.</li>
        <li>We disclose our affiliate relationship on every page that carries affiliate links.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Spotted an error, or a spec that has changed? Want to suggest a model we should cover? Email <strong>hello@thebestmowers.co.uk</strong> and we will put it right.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
